<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFABFFB8C6F45704FEB9F9F1" bold="true" box="[199,308,1591,1617]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Remarks</emphasis>
. The new species seems a little similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFABFFB8C527570BFC23F9F1" authority="Liu &amp; Disney, 2022" authorityName="Liu &amp; Disney" authorityYear="2022" box="[788,942,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parviflavus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFABFFB8C527570BFC23F9F1" box="[788,942,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">P. parviflavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFABFFB8C5855704FB9DF9F1" bold="true" box="[950,1040,1591,1617]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25C4700FFABFFB8C5855704FB9DF9F1" box="[950,1040,1591,1617]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
It differs from the latter by shorter setal palisade of mid tibia, longer setulae of sternite VI and brownish body colour.
</paragraph>
